Middlesbrough Women.
<a href="Middlesbrough%20F.C.%20Women">Middlesbrough Women</a> is the women's football club affiliated to Middlesbrough. Founded as Cleveland Spartans in 1976, they became officially affiliated with the men's team in 2023, and currently play in the <a href="FA%20Women%27s%20National%20League">FA Women's National League Division One North</a>, the fourth level of <a href="Women%27s%20football%20in%20England%23Pyramid">English women's football</a>.
